TASK_DESCRIPTION=Redesign Doey's task system TUI (the Go dashboard task view) with inspiration from three Charmbracelet exemplars. Goal: simple, elegant, glamorous — subtract rather than add. Better layout distribution, elevated UX, polished feel. NOT a feature dump — a refinement pass.

INSPIRATION SOURCES (must study source code first):
1. Kancli (github.com/charmbracelet/kancli) — Kanban layout architecture, column focus/blur, clean borders, task movement feel
2. omm (github.com/dhth/omm) — Radical simplicity, theming, prefix filtering, the "just enough" philosophy
3. Zachkp/todo (github.com/zachkp/todo) — Visual design, sub-todo progress indicators, multi-view elegance

DESIGN PRINCIPLES:
- Simple > feature-rich. Remove noise before adding chrome
- Better layout distribution — use available terminal space intelligently
- Glamorous = polished details (spacing, alignment, color harmony, transitions)
- Stay true to Doey's existing architecture — enhance, don't rebuild

PHASES:
Phase 1 (Research): Clone/study Kancli, omm, Zachkp/todo source. Extract specific patterns worth adopting — layout math, color schemes, component composition, UX micro-interactions
Phase 2 (Design): Propose concrete changes to Doey's task TUI. Diff against current state. Keep it minimal
Phase 3 (Implement): Apply changes. One worker per file. Validate rendering at common terminal sizes

SUCCESS CRITERIA:
- Task view looks noticeably more polished and spacious
- No new features added that aren't in the inspiration sources
- Existing task functionality preserved (list, add, transition, subtasks)
- Clean at 80x24 and 120x40 terminal sizes
